3.0 of 5 bubbles
Interesting Museum
Oct 2019 • Solo
In looking to kill some time whilst in Da Nang, I decided to visit the Museum of Cham Sculpture. Entry cost was 60K VND. As with similar museums, to get the most out of it it is probably worthwhile hiring a guide or at best, hiring the audio. There are 3 main areas to the musuem and some of the sculptures are truly amazing. Set aside approximatley 1 - 2 hours for your visit.
I had visited the My Son site last year and alot of the artefacts/sculptures within the museum are from this site. On a side note, I stronly recommend you visit My Son if you have the opportunity to do so.
Well worth the visit especially if you have some time on your hands whilst in Da Nang. For some reason, the portable airconditioners located throughout the museum were turned off when I visited. Whilst there were fans on, I still found that inside the museum it was quite hot so come prepared.
Written October 24, 2019
