Written September 21, 2019
Govindan N
Bengaluru, India2,786 contributions
Wonderful Experience
May 2019
This museum has the world’s largest collection of Cham artefacts., it displays more than 300 pieces including Shiva lingas garudas, apsaras Ganesha and images of Shiva, Brahma and Vishnu, all dating from the 5th to 15th centuries. There are also exhibits focusing on Cham culture today. The museum also displays terracotta and stone works of art .In addition to the Hindu-influenced pieces there are also some that have evidently drawn inspiration from Buddhism including altars and deities.
The Museum of Cham Sculpture Opening Hours: Daily from 07:00-17:00.A good place to visit in Danang. Entrance Fee -60000 VND.
